Name: VHIL_N600_VehFunc_EngTemp_OverTempWarning_Urban_01
Test Case Description: Verify high engine temperature warning when OVER_TEMPERATURE_INDICATION is active via CAN in Urban Mode
Pre-Action:
1. Battery connected
2. Set the Voltage 13.5V
3. Turn Ignition ON.[Ignition_SW_IP = 1]
4. Crank the vehicle [ES_SW_IP=1]
5. No CAN Failure should not be present
6. Set ride mode as URBAN
Test Steps.Action:
1. Simulate Engine_Coolant_Temperature = 110 deg C
1.1  CAN message should have  ENGINE_DATA_2 (0x350): OVER_TEMPERATURE_INDICATION = 1 and ENGINE_DATA_2 (0x350): ENGINE_TEMPERATURE= 110
1.2 Cluster should display "HIGH COOLANT TEMPERATURE" warning for 3 seconds.
1.3. The colorbar in soft telltale should be in Red Colour and the hard telltale should glow
Post-Action:
1. Turn Ignition OFF.[Ignition_SW_IP = 0]



2. Set the Voltage 0V
